50|$|Power <b>hacksaws</b> {{are not as}} {{commonly}} used in the metalworking industries as they once were. Bandsaws and cold saws have mostly displaced them. While stationary electric <b>hacksaws</b> are not very common, they are still produced. Power <b>hacksaws</b> of the type powered by stationary engines and line shafts, like other line-shaft-powered machines, are now rare; museums and antique-tool hobbyists still preserve a few of them.|$|R
