25|$|The {{feature film}} <b>Hacksaw</b> Ridge, {{based on his}} life, was {{produced}} by Terry Benedict and directed by Mel Gibson. The film was released nationwide in the U.S. on November 4, 2016 to positive reviews. Doss is portrayed by Andrew Garfield, who was nominated for an Academy Award for Best Actor for his performance. Desmond's wife, Dorothy, is played by Teresa Palmer.|$|E
25|$|Cunanan next {{drove to}} Chicago and killed 72-year-old Lee Miglin, a {{prominent}} real estate developer, on May 4, 1997. Miglin had been bound {{with duct tape}} {{on his hands and}} feet and wrapped around his head. He was then stabbed over 20 times with a screwdriver and had his throat sawed open with a <b>hacksaw.</b> Following this murder, the FBI added Cunanan to its Ten Most Wanted list.|$|E
